    <note>Fang(1) Chou [23969] Chou is the first Xinzhou Fang jinshi. Shiyin [601] held a title when he earned the jinshi in 1148 at age 49 and, according to Jiangxi TZ, moved to Yushan. Chou vilified Qin(1) Gui [8008] and, as a result, was purged and exiled. Shiyin appears in executive finance in 1156, after Qin(1) Gui's death. All the evidence points to a kinship relationship between Chou and Shiyin. They may even be brothers, but I am making Chou a nephew of Shiyin's father, Yun [23968]. CBD, 1, 67.</note>
